  "prompt": "How can you avoid a girl who has a huge crush on you without hurting her?",
  "response": "Navigating a situation where someone has a crush on you can be delicate, especially if you want to avoid hurting their feelings. Here are some strategies you can consider:\n\n1. **Be Honest but Kind**: If you feel comfortable, gently let her know that you don't share the same feelings. Emphasize that you value her as a person and appreciate her friendship.\n\n2. **Limit One-on-One Time**: Gradually reduce the amount of time you spend alone together. This can help send a subtle signal without needing to have an explicit conversation.\n\n3. **Group Activities**: Encourage group outings where you can interact more casually. This can help shift the dynamic and make it less intense.\n\n4. **Focus on Friendship**: Show that you value her as a friend. Engage in conversations about mutual interests, which can help reinforce a platonic relationship.\n\n5. **Encourage Her Interests**: Support her in pursuing hobbies or friendships that don\u2019t involve you. This can help her shift her focus away from you.\n\n6. **Be Respectful and Compassionate**: Understand that crushes can be tough to deal with. Be respectful in your interactions and avoid actions that might lead her on.\n\n7. **Non-Verbal Cues**: Sometimes, non-verbal communication can help set boundaries. Maintain a friendly but more reserved demeanor if you sense that she is getting mixed signals.\n\n8. **Set Boundaries**: If necessary, politely clarify your boundaries if she crosses them, ensuring that your message is clear but gentle.\n\nUltimately, being empathetic while communicating your feelings clearly is key to avoiding unnecessary hurt. Remember that it's natural for people to have crushes, and being considerate can go a long way.",
